article.description: Air Force holds on to edge Wyoming 55-53
article.headline: Air Force holds on to edge Wyoming 55-53
article.linkText: Air Force holds on to edge Wyoming 55-53
article.story: LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Tre' Coggins scored 20 points and Max Yon added 14, including two late go-ahead free throws, as Air Force held on for a 55-53 win over Wyoming on Tuesday. Nathan Sobey had 18 points to pace Wyoming (17-11, 8-7 Mountain West), while Jerron Granberry added 14 and Josh Adams 11. Air Force (11-15, 5-10) won for only the second time in 10 games. Yon's two free throws with 2:37 left put the Falcons ahead 51-50, and after Granberry was called for a charging foul, Yon added two more foul shots at the 1:47 mark. After a Coggins free throw made it 54-50, Adams drained a 3 with 13.6 seconds left to trim the lead to 54-53. Kamryn Williams made 1 of 2 free throws for Air Force with 11.7 seconds remaining and Sobey missed a 3 just before the buzzer.
